Write 4 new Playwright E2E test files and extend 1 existing file for the Adelie Investment frontend.

The app is mobile-first (max-width 480px), Korean UI, React 19 + Vite. The Playwright config uses baseURL `http://localhost:3001` with 10 projects (1 desktop + 9 mobile devices).

## File 1: `frontend/e2e/agent-canvas-v5.spec.js` (~6 tests)

Agent Canvas page is at `/agent`. Components: ChatInput, StatusIndicator, AgentSessionPanel, AgentHubHeader, AgentChatThread.

```javascript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test.describe('V5: Agent Canvas v5', () => {
  test.beforeEach(async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto('/agent');
    await page.waitForLoadState('networkidle').catch(() => {});
  });

  // V5-01: Page renders without ErrorBoundary crash
  // Check that /agent page loads, no "문제가 발생했습니다" error text
  // ChatInput (input or textarea) should be visible

  // V5-02: ChatInput focus
  // Click on input → it should be focused

  // V5-03: StatusIndicator shows "대기"
  // Look for text "대기" on the page

  // V5-04: Session panel toggle
  // Look for a session panel trigger button, click it, verify panel appears/disappears

  // V5-05: Empty state shows recommended questions
  // Check for suggested question chips/buttons

  // V5-06: AgentHubHeader renders mode context
  // Header should show mode-related UI
});
```

## File 2: `frontend/e2e/slash-commands.spec.js` (~7 tests)

The SlashCommandMenu appears when user types "/" in the ChatInput on `/agent` page.

```javascript
// SC-01: "/" shows menu popup
// SC-02: Korean alias "/시각화" → highlights chart command
// SC-03: Filtering - "/ch" shows only matching commands
// SC-04: Arrow keys move highlight
// SC-05: Enter selects command
// SC-06: 15+ items rendered in menu
// SC-07: Navigation command /포트폴리오 → navigates to /portfolio
```

For testing slash commands, type "/" in the agent input, wait for the popup menu to appear.

## File 3: `frontend/e2e/flashcard-education.spec.js` (~4 tests)

Education page is at `/education`. FlashCardList component shows saved flashcards.

```javascript
// FC-01: FlashCardList section renders on Education page
// FC-02: Empty state shows "복습카드가 없어요" or similar empty message
// FC-03: Delete button has aria-label="삭제"
// FC-04: Network error doesn't crash the page
```

## File 4: `frontend/e2e/page-modular-regression.spec.js` (~5 tests)

Verify that modularized pages render their sub-components correctly.

```javascript
// MOD-01: Home sub-components (Schedule, Carousel, Cards sections)
// MOD-02: Education sub-components (Calendar/Quiz/FlashCard/Review sections)
// MOD-03: Narrative STEP UI renders
// MOD-04: 5 pages load without ErrorBoundary: /, /home, /education, /search, /agent
// MOD-05: BottomNav tab switching works
```

## File 5: Extend `frontend/e2e/agent-canvas-mobile.spec.js` (+4 tests)

Add these tests AFTER the existing FE-AGENT-M04 test:

```javascript
// M05: ChatInput fits in iPhone SE viewport
// M06: StatusIndicator shows dot + label on mobile
// M07: SlashMenu doesn't overflow viewport
// M08: FlashCardList on /education has no horizontal scroll
```

IMPORTANT notes for all files:
- Use `test.beforeEach` with `page.goto()` and `page.waitForLoadState('networkidle').catch(() => {})`
- Tests should be resilient: use `.catch(() => false)` for `isVisible()` checks
- Use `test.skip()` when a component doesn't exist (graceful degradation)
- Use descriptive Korean+English test IDs
- Import from `@playwright/test`

